            <title>[HBASE-159] [hbase] If master asks region server to shut down, by-pass return of shutdown message</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-159</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If master tells cluster to shut down, currently region servers hang on the exit.  They are trying return to the exited-master a report that they are on the way out.  This report should not be sent in this scenario.  Here&apos;s a log excerpt:&lt;/p&gt;

